Nigerian serial entrepreneur and the Chief Executive Officer of Aremo Oba Autos, a leading auto firms in the country, Adeshina Jelili Oladipupo, popularly known as Aremo, has advised Nigerians on the need to make honesty a priority, mostly in business dealings, just as he charged the youths to be diligent and hardworking. Speaking with newsmen in Lagos, on Thursday, Oladipupo, revealed his passion for entrepreneurship from childhood, which he claimed it spurred him to venture into the automobile business in 2016. Fulfill Oyo 2019 coalition agreements, ADC candidates charge… PDP governors congratulate Duoye Diri Proscribed NURTW leaders warn Oyo govt against introduction… Reps demand records on CBN revenues, capital projects “My passion for entrepreneurship helped me to thrive in the business despite the challenging environment of the industry. As a business-oriented person, who wanted to invest my savings in one business, I went into auto-business. Some friends assisted me to actualise my dream. My sojourn to South Africa also helped me in the business,” he added. ALSO READ: ITF trains 316 youths in multiple trade areas While highlighting the challenges of establishing as well as sustaining challenges of business in Nigeria, Oladipupo advised youths not to be discouraged, hence, to be hardworking and persevere as success would come their way. SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE TO GET IT!!! STAY STRONGER, LONGER AND SATISFY MADAM LIKE NEVER BEFORE WITH THIS NATURAL SUPPLEMENTS WITH NO SIDE EFFECTS. CLICK NOW. CLICK HERE NOW TO WORK FROM HOME ENTIRELY AT YOUR OWN CONVINIENCE AND GET PAID WEEKLY, DIRECTLY INTO YOUR SPECIFIED BANK ACCOUNT.REGISTRATION IS ABSOLUTELY FREE.